post_text: Nebraska CAPS Student Career Project Presentation Days are scheduled! Please join us for an afternoon of achievements as students showcase their semester-long work as part of the Nebraska CAPS program. Sandy Creek students will present from 1:00-4:40 on Wednesday December 6. Lawrence Nelson students will present from 1:00-3:40 on Wednesday, December 13. These presentations are open to the public and we welcome anybody who would like to witness and learn about the student accomplishments. For specific times and schedules see the attached images.

shared_text:
Nebraska CAPS added 2 new photos.
April 7, 2017 at 1:24 PM ·

On April 5, students involved in the NCAPS Health Career Pathway attended the Health Career Expo at Central Community College in Hastings, NE. Students were exposed to 9 different careers in health care and participated in lots of hand-on activities. Our students were able to visit with staff and professionals in the fields of occupational therapy, dental hygiene and dental assisting, paramedic medicine, nursing, certified nursing assistant, medical assisting and medical technician. They were also able to explore the inside of an ambulance and medical helicopter and visit with the professionals that save lives on these vehicles!

post_text:
Nebraska CAPS graphic arts and publishing pathway students had the opportunity to work hands on with our business partner Hastings Tribune. A big thank you goes to the Hastings Tribune for being a great business partner for Nebraska CAPS and giving our students many real world work experiences throughout the year. Check out the article and photography by Katrina A, Brianna S, and Kaytlynn T here - http://www.hastingstribune.com/news/students-try-to-make-all-the-right-moves-at-chess/article_a6012eb8-1686-11e7-9cd8-ab326057ea47.html
The article was published on the front page of the Hastings Tribune on April 1st, 2017.
